Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.3 percent to 7,074.82, halting a
three-day retreat. The gauge has declined 21 percent this year,
set for the first annual drop since 2008.  Formosa Plastics Group units:  Formosa Plastics Corp. (1301)  (1301
TT) slipped 2.4 percent to NT$80.8.  Nan Ya Plastics Corp. (1303)  (1303
TT) fell 1.2 percent to NT$59.7.  Formosa Chemicals & Fibre Corp. (1326) 
(1326 TT) slumped 1.4 percent to NT$79.7.  Formosa Plastics Group Chairman William Wong said heâ€™s
downbeat about the industry outlook for the first and second
quarters, according to a statement after markets closed
yesterday.  Compeq Manufacturing Co. (2313)  (2313 TT), a maker of printed
circuit boards, added 1.6 percent to NT$9.4. The company plans
to invest $45 million to set up a new company in Chongqing,
southwestern  China , according to a statement to exchange.  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT), a light-emitting diode maker,
gained 0.6 percent to NT$64.7. The company plans to buy back 10
million shares, according to a statement to the stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
